A missing 3-year-old girl from Cape Town has been found alive on Tuesday.Asaza Sauls from Kraaifontein went missing on, August 27, at 11.20am when she left with her sister&#8217;s mother but not returned home.Police spokesperson FC van Wyk said Sauls went missing with her mother&#8217;s sister.&#8220;Sauls has been found safe and unharmed in Philippi,&#8221; he said.Pink ladies for missing minors organisation said all the necessary medication will take place however they thank everyone for sharing flyers of the little one.TNA Reporter &nbsp;